	<Title>
		Neck size: Better than BMI for kids?
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		Neck size &amp;mdash; A Mayo Clinic specialist discusses using neck size to gauge childhood obesity.
	</Abstract>
	<Question>
		Is a child&apos;s neck size a better way to gauge childhood obesity than body mass index (BMI)?
	</Question>
